  Two things matter a lot and I want to be precise (no guessing):

  1. Blackwell (sm_120) needs CUDA 12.8+ and a recent PyTorch cu128 build. Older torch wheels won't run on a 5090 at all. We'll install from the cu128 index.
  2. Python 3.14 (Store stub) is the wrong interpreter — PyTorch/diffusers wheels lag new Python releases, and the Store build sandboxes pip. We want a real Python 3.12 venv.

  With 32 GB VRAM we have way more headroom than the L4 plan: we can do full fine-tuning of SD 1.5 at 512px (not just LoRA), bigger batches, and a higher-res from-scratch DDPM (64px, maybe a latent model).
